quran[7]{c,v,t}:
  5,20,"And (remember) when Musa said to his people: \"O my people! Remember the favor of Allah to you: when He made Prophets among you, made you kings and gave you what He had not given to any other among the nations (Al-`Alamin)"
  5,21,O my people! Enter the Holy Land which Allah has assigned to you and turn not back; for then you will be returned as losers
  5,22,"They said: \"O Musa! In it are a people of great strength, and we shall never enter it, till they leave it; when they leave, then we will enter"
  5,23,"Two men of those who feared (Allah and) on whom Allah had bestowed His grace said: \"Assault them through the gate; for when you are in, victory will be yours. And put your trust in Allah if you are believers indeed"
  5,24,"They said: \"O Musa! We shall never enter it as long as they are there. So go, you and your Lord, and fight you two, we are sitting right here"
  5,25,"He [Musa] said: \"O my Lord! I have power only over myself and my brother, so Ifruq us from the rebellious people"
  5,26,"(Allah) said: \"Therefore it is forbidden to them for forty years; in distraction they will wander through the land. So do not greive for the rebellious people"